          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "Found the root cause.\n\n**The loop:**\n1. App starts → `AuthProvider` mounts → `refreshAuth()` calls `GET /auth/me`\n2. Not logged in, so `/auth/me` returns 401\n3. `api.ts` sees 401, and since `/auth/me` is **not** in `NO_REFRESH_ENDPOINTS`, it tries `POST /auth/refresh`\n4. Refresh fails (no valid token) → `window.location.href = \"/login\"` (line 86/92) — full page reload\n5. App restarts → `refreshAuth()` runs again → same loop forever\n\nThe fix: add `/auth/me` to `NO_REFRESH_ENDPOINTS`. When the session-check endpoint returns 401, it means the user simply isn't logged in — no refresh needed. The `refreshAuth` catch block already handles this correctly by calling `clearAuth()`.",
